correctness.rationale: The extraction contains many values that are not reported in the article, several schema/unit violations, and factual inconsistencies. Specific issues: (1) Schema violations/formatting: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null but must be an object or omitted; deviceProperties.subthresholdSwing uses unit MilliV but the numeric value 0.13 corresponds to 0.13 mV/dec instead of the reported 0.13 V/dec (should be 130 mV); electricalProperties.carrierDensity uses ElectricChargeVolumeDensity with unit C-PER-M3 and an unconverted numeric value (should be PER-M3 if giving number density). (2) Ungrounded/guessed process parameters: reactor.manufacturer listed as 'South Korea' (article only states apparatus “CN1, South Korea”; manufacturer not given); pressure (10 mTorr), deliveryMethod, dosingTime (1000 ms), flowRates (sccm values), supercycleDesign counts (10/5/3) and sequence, nucleationPeriod (5 cycles), numberofCycles (100) are not reported; carrierGas/purgingGas N2 are not specified in the text; growthPerCycle values are not given in the article. (3) Material properties not supported: refractiveIndex (1.9), absorptionCoefficient (0.05), filmDensity (5.2 g/dm3) are not reported; bandGap 3.3 eV corresponds to a 13 nm boost layer, not to the bilayer or base layer; uniformity (5%) and conformality (aspect ratio 10) are unreported. (4) Film composition errors: elementalConcentration is provided as a single 60% value rather than per element; atomicRatio '1.0:2.8:5.4' contradicts Table 1 (bilayer average atom% ~ In 60, Ga 21, Zn 19). (5) Electrical properties misattribution: electricalProperties.mobility 74 cm^2/Vs is labeled as Hall measurements but the 74 value is the device μ_FE; resistivity is not reported. (6) Device properties: fieldEffectMobility 74.0 cm^2/Vs, V_TH 0.20 V, and ION/OFF ~3.2×10^8 match the bilayer with 4 nm Al2O3/50 nm HfO2, and deviceStructure (top-gate staggered) is correct; roughness 0.67 nm matches the bilayer AFM. (7) Multiple processes: the article reports distinct base, boost, and bilayer IGZO films; only a single process is extracted, losing the supercycle design/composition differences across processes. Corrections needed: remove or leave unspecified all unreported parameters (pressure, flow rates, dosing times, nucleation period, supercycle counts, delivery method, carrier/purge gas); fix SS to 130 mV; correct carrier density units and value appropriate to the film/process (or omit if not reported for bilayer); correct film composition to match Table 1 (e.g., bilayer average In 60 at.%, Ga 21 at.%, Zn 19 at.% and a consistent atomic ratio); do not label μ_FE as Hall; remove unreported optical/density/uniformity/conformality values; correct reactor fields; and consider extracting separate processes for base, boost, and bilayer depositions.

completeness.rationale: Very poor completeness and schema adherence. (1) Missing processes: The article reports at least three distinct ALD IGZO depositions (single-layer base In0.52Ga0.29Zn0.19O, single-layer boost In0.82Ga0.08Zn0.10O, and a bilayer 3 nm boost/10 nm base). Only one process is extracted, so two processes are missing. (2) Numerous untraceable/fabricated parameters: carrier/purging gas (N2), reactor pressure (10 mTorr), dosing times (1 s), flow rates (sccm), nucleation period (5 cycles), number of cycles (100), growth-per-cycle values, supercycle subcycle counts (10/5/3), uniformity (5%), conformality aspect ratio (10), refractive index (1.9), absorption coefficient (0.05), and film density (5.2 g/dm3) are not reported in the paper. (3) Schema and unit issues: plasmaPower is present as null (violates schema—omit if not used), subthreshold swing is given as 0.13 with unit mV (should be 130 mV to represent 0.13 V/dec per article and schema unit), electrical carrierDensity uses C/m3 with an incorrect magnitude (article gives 1.3×10^18 cm^-3 for the boost film; in SI this is ~1.3×10^24 m^-3, and unit should be PER-M3 if number density), reactor.manufacturer set to “South Korea” (not a manufacturer). (4) Misalignment with reported data: materialProperties.mobility is listed as 74 cm^2/Vs with “Hall effect measurements” (74 is device μ_FE for the bilayer with Al2O3/HfO2; Hall mobility was ~73 cm^2/Vs only for the 13 nm boost film), optical band gap set to 3.3 eV with method “UV-Vis” (article states band gap by spectroscopic ellipsometry; 3.65 eV base, 3.30 eV 13 nm boost, 3.51 eV for 3 nm boost), elemental atomic ratio ‘1.0:2.8:5.4’ does not match reported compositions (bilayer average ~In:Ga:Zn = 60:21:19 at.%). (5) Some correct/traceable items exist (precursors DADI/TMGa/DEZ; O3; substrate temperature 250 °C; purge time 10 s; roughness 0.67 nm; bilayer amorphous; device metrics μ_FE 74 cm^2/Vs, V_TH ≈ 0.2 V, I_ON/OFF ≈ 3.2×10^8; top-gate staggered), but overall the record contains many inaccuracies and guesses. Actions: add separate processes for base, boost, and bilayer; remove null plasmaPower; correct SS unit/value (130 mV); correct carrier density units/values; report band gaps and methods per article; correct composition ratios; and omit parameters not supported by the text or mark as unavailable if schema permits.
